obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (14608)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14608&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Railway Protection`
  line `Force Act, 1957.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 10th September 1959, vide notification No. 58-security/16/9, dated 10-9-1959, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, s. 1.`
  line `Extended to Goa, Daman and Diu with modifications, by Reg. 12 of 1962, s. 3 and Schedule.`
  line `The Act comes into force in Pondicherry on 1-10-1963, s. 3 and Schedule I.`
  line `Extended to and brought into force in Dadra and Nagar Haveli (w.e.f. 1-7-1965) by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Schedule I.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (14609)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14609&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Force" means the Railway Protection Force constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) "Director-General" means the Director-General of the Force appointed under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 4;`
  line
  line `(ba) "enrolled member of the Force" means any subordinate officer, under officer or any other`
  line `member of the Force of a rank lower than that of under officer;`
  line
  line `(bb) "Force custody" means the arrest or confinement of a member of the Force in accordance`
  line `with rules made under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(c) "member of the Force" means a person appointed to the Force under this Act ^3* * *;`
  line
  line `^4[(ca) "passenger" shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989)`
  line
  line `(cb) "passenger area" shall include railway platform, train, yard and such other area as is`
  line `frequently visited by passengers;]`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" mean prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "railway property" includes any goods, money or valuable security, or animal, belonging to,`
  line `or in the charge or possession of, a railway administration;`
  line
  line `^5[(ea) "subordinate officer" means a person appointed to the Force as an Inspector, Sub-Inspector`
  line `or an Assistant Sub-Inspector;]`
  line
  line `(f) "superior officer" means any of the officers appointed under section 4 and includes any other`
  line `officer appointed by the Central Government as a superior officer of the Force;`
  line
  line `^6[(fa) "under officer" means a person appointed to the Force as a Head Constable or Naik;]`
  line
  line `(g) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Indian Railways`
  line `Act, 1890 (9 of 1890), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them under that Act.`
  line
  line `^6[(2) Any reference in this act to a law which is not in force in any area shall in relation to that area,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 2 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 60 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 20-9-85).`
  line
  line `3. The words "other than a superior officer" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 52 of 2003, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 60 of 1985, s. 3(w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 60 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (14610)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14610&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted and maintained by the Central`
  line `Government a ^1[an armed Force of the Union] to be called the Railway Protection Force for the better`
  line `protection and security of railway property.`
  line
  line `(2) The force shall be constituted in such manner shall consist of such number of ^2[superior`
  line `officers subordinate officers, under officers and other enrolled members] of the Force and shall receive`
  line `such pay and other renumeration as maybe prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "a Force" (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "superior officers and members" (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (14611)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment and powers of superior officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14611&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Central Government may appoint a`
  line `person to be the Director-General of the Force and may appoint other persons to be Inspector-General,`
  line `Additional Inspector-General, Deputy Inspector-General, Assistant Inspector-General, Senior`
  line `Commandants, Commandants or Assistant Commandants of the Force.]`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[Director-General] and every other superior officer so appointed shall posses and exercise`
  line `such powers and authority over the members of the Force under their respective commands as is provided`
  line `by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "Inspector-General" (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (14612)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14612&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `5. [Classes and ranks among members of the Force.]--Omitted by the Railway Protection Force`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1985 (60 of 1985), s. 6 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (14613)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Appointment of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. bys. 7, ibid., for s. 6 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14613&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Appointment of members of the Force.--The appointment of enrolled members of the Force`
  line `shall rest with the Inspector-General, Additional Inspector-General or Deputy Inspector-General who`
  line `shall exercise that power in accordance with rules made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the power of appointment under this section may also be exercised by other superior`
  line `officer as the Inspector-General, Additional Inspector-General or Deputy Inspector-General concerned`
  line `may, by order, specify in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (14614)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Certificates to members of the Forces.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14614&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every member of the Force shall receive on his`
  line `appointment a certificate in the form specified in the Schedule, under the seal of the ^1[Inspector-General,`
  line `Additional Inspector-General or Deputy Inspector-General] or such other superior officer as the`
  line a
  line `^1[Inspector-General, Additional Inspector-General or Deputy Inspector-General] may specify in this`
  line `behalf by virtue of which the person holding such certificate shall be vested with the powers of a member`
  line `of the Force.`
  line
  line `(2) Such certificate shall cease to have effect whenever the person named in it ceases for any reason`
  line `to be a member of the Force^2* * *.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "Chief Security Officer" (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (14615)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Superintendence and administration of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 60 of 1985 s. 9, for section 8 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14615&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Superintendence and administration of the Force.--(1) The superintendence of the Force shall`
  line `vest in the Central Government, and subject thereto and to the provisions of this Act and of any rules`
  line `made thereunder, the command supervision and administration of the Force shall vest in the DirectorGeneral.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the administration of the Force, within such local`
  line `limits in relation to a railway as may be prescribed shall be carried on by an Inspector-General, an`
  line `Additional Inspector-General or a Deputy Inspector-General in accordance with the provisions of this Act`
  line `and of any rules made thereunder and they shall, subject to any direction that may be given by the Central`
  line `Government or the Director-General in this behalf discharge his function under the general supervision of`
  line `the General Manager of the Railway.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (14616)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Dismissal, removal, etc., of members of the force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14616&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of article 311 of`
  line `the Constitution and to such rules as the Central Government may make under this Act, any superior`
  line `officer may--`
  line
  line `(i) dismiss, suspend or reduce in rank any ^1[enrolled member] of the Force whom he shall think`
  line `remiss or negligent in the discharge of his duty, or unfit for the same; or`
  line
  line `(ii) award any one or more of the following punishments to any ^2[enrolled member] of the Force`
  line `who discharges his duty in a careless or negligent manner, or who by any act of his own renders`
  line `himself unfit for the discharge thereof, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) fine to any amount not exceeding seven day's pay or reduction in pay scale;`
  line
  line `(b) confinement to quarters for a period not exceeding fourteen days with or without`
  line `punishment, drill, extra guard, fatigue or other duty;`
  line
  line `(c) removal from any office of distinction or deprivation of any special emolument.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Any enrolled member of the force aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1) may, within`
  line `within thirty days from the date on which the order is communicated to him prefer an appeal against the`
  line `order to such authority as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the prescribed authority may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in`
  line time.
  line
  line `(3)In disposing of the appeal, the prescribed authority shall follow such procedure as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order imposing an enhanced penalty under sub-section (2) shall be made unless a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard has been given to the person affected by such order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1985 s. 9, for section 8 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs.bys. 10, ibid., for "member" (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 20-9-1985)`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (14617)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers and members of the Force to be deemed to be railway servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 18 and the Schedule, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14617&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line ^1[Director-General
  line `and every member of the Force] shall for all purposes be regarded as railway servants with the meaning of`
  line `the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890), other than Chapter VIA thereof, and shall be entitled to`
  line `exercise the powers conferred on railway servants by or under that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (14618)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duties of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 52 of 2003, s. 4, for section 11 (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14618&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Duties of members of the Force.-- It shall be the duty of every superior officer and member of`
  line `the Force--`
  line
  line `(a) promptly to execute all orders lawfully issued to him by his superior authority;`
  line
  line `(b) to protect and safeguard railway property, passenger area and passengers;`
  line
  line `(c) to remove any obstruction in the movement of railway property or passenger area; and`
  line
  line `(d) to do any other act conducive to the better protection and security of railway property,`
  line `passenger area and passengers.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (14619)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to arrest without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14619&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Power to arrest without warrant.--Any member of the Force may, without an order from a`
  line `Magistrate and without a warrant, arrest--`
  line
  line `(i) any person who voluntarily causes hurt to, or attempts voluntarily to cause hurt to, or`
  line `wrongfully restrains or attempts wrongfully to restrain, or assaults, threatens to assault, or uses, or`
  line `threatens or attempts to use, criminal force to him or any other member of the Force in the execution`
  line `of his duty as such member, or with intent to prevent or to deter him from discharging his duty as`
  line `such member, or in consequence of anything done or attempted to be done by him in the lawful`
  line `discharge of his duty as such member; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any person who has been concerned in, or against whom a reasonable suspicion exists of his`
  line `having been concerned in, or who is found taking precautions to conceal his presence under`
  line `circumstances which afford reason to believe that he is taking such precautions with a view to`
  line `committing a cognizable offence which relates to ^2[railway property, passenger area and passengers];`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) any person found taking precautions to conceal his presence within the railway limits under`
  line `circumstances which afford reason to believe that he is taking such precautions with a view to`
  line `committing theft of, or damage to, ^2[railway property, passenger area and passengers]; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any person who commits or attempts to commit a cognizable offence which involves or`
  line `which is likely to involve imminent danger to the life of any person engaged in carrying on any work`
  line `relating to ^2[railway property, passenger area and passengers].]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1985, s. 11, for section 12 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 52 of 2003, s. 5, for "railway property" (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (14620)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to search without warrant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14620&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1)Whenever ^1*** any member of the Force, not below the`
  line `rank of a Senior Rakshak, has reason to believe that any such offence as is referred to in section 12 has`
  line `been or is being committed and that a search-warrant cannot be obtained without affording the offender`
  line `an opportunity of escaping or of concealing evidence of the offence, he may detain him and search his`
  line `person and belongings forthwith and, if he thinks proper, arrest any person whom he has reason to believe`
  line `to have committed the offence.`
  line
  line `(2)The provisions of the ^2[Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], relating to searches under`
  line `that Code shall, so far as may be, apply to searches under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "any superior officer or" omitted by Act 60 of 1985, s. 18 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 18 and Schedule, ibid., for "Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (14621)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Procedure to be followed after arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14621&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any ^1*** member of the Force making an arrest under`
  line `this Act, shall, without unnecessary delay, make over the person so arrested ^2`
  line `[to a police officer together`
  line `with a detailed report of the circumstances leading to the arrest of such persons], or in the absence of a`
  line `police officer, take such person or cause him to be taken to the nearest police station.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "superior officer or" omitted by s. 18 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 52 of 2003, s. 6, for "to a police officer" (w.e.f. 1-7-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (14622)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Officers and members of the Force to be considered always on duty and liable to be employed in any part of the railways.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14622&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every member of the Force shall, for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, be considered to be always on duty, and shall, at any time, be liable to be employed at any place`
  line `within India.]`
  line
  line `(2) No ^2* * * member of the Force shall engage himself in any employment or office other than his`
  line `duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1985, s. 12, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. The words "superior officer or" omitted by Act 60 of 1985, s. 12 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (14623)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 16
  title `Restrictions respecting right to Form association, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14623&sectionno=15A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Restrictions respecting right to Form association, etc.--(1) No member of the Force shall,`
  line `without the previous sanction in writing of the Central Government or of the prescribed authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any trade union, labour union, political`
  line `association or with any class of trade unions, labour unions or political associations; or`
  line
  line `(b) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any other society, institution, association or`
  line `organisation that is not recognised as part of the Force or is not of a purely social, recreational or`
  line `religious nature; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate with the press or publish or cause to be published any book, letter or other`
  line `document except where such communication or publication is in the bona fide discharge of his duties`
  line `or is of a purely literary, artistic or scientific character or is of a prescribed nature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--If any question arises as to whether any society, institution, association or organisation`
  line `is of a purely social, recreational or religious nature under clause (b) of this sub-section, the decision of`
  line `the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of the Force shall participate in, or address, any meeting or take part in any`
  line `demonstration organised by any body of persons for any political purposes or for such other purposes as`
  line `may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (14624)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Responsibilities of members of the Force during suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14624&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `A member of the Force shall`
  line `not by reason of his suspension from office cease to be a member of the Force; and he shall, during that`
  line `period, be subject to the same responsibilities, discipline and penalties to which he would have been`
  line `subject if he were on duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (14625)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 18
  title `Surrender of certificate, arms, etc., by persons ceasing to be members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14625&sectionno=16A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Surrender of certificate, arms, etc., by persons ceasing to be members of the Force.--(1)`
  line `Every person who for any reason ceases to be a member of the Force, shall forthwith surrender to any`
  line `superior officer empowered to receive the same, his certificate of appointment, the arms, accoutrements,`
  line `clothing and other articles which have been furnished to him for the performance of his duties as a`
  line `member of the Force.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who wilfully neglects or refuses to surrender his certificate of appointment, the arms,`
  line `accoutrements, clothing and other articles furnished to him, as required by sub-section (1) shall on`
  line `conviction, be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to two hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to apply to any article which, under the orders of the`
  line `Director-General, has become the property of the person to whom the same was furnished.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (14626)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Penalties for neglect of duty, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs.by s. 15, ibid., for section 17 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14626&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Penalties for neglect of duty, etc.-- (1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in`
  line `section 9, every enrolled member of the Force who shall be guilty of any violation of duty or wilful`
  line `breach or neglect of any rule or lawful order made by a superior officer, or who shall withdraw from`
  line `duties of his office without permission, or who, being absent on leave, fails, without reasonable cause, to`
  line `report himself for duty on the expiration of the leave, or who engages himself without authority for any`
  line `employment other than his duty as an enrolled member of the Force, or who shall be guilty of cowardice may be taken into Force custody and shall, on conviction, be punished with imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to one year.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1973), an`
  line `offence punishable under this section shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1973), the`
  line `Central Government may invest Assistant Inspector-General, Senior Commandant or Commandant with`
  line `the powers of a Magistrate of any class for the purpose of inquiring into or trying any offence committed`
  line `by an enrolled member of the Force and punishable under this Act, or any offence committed by an`
  line `enrolled member of the Force against the person or property of another member of the Force:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) when the offender is on leave or absent from duty; or`
  line
  line `(ii) when the offence is not connected with the offender's duties as an enrolled member of the`
  line `Force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) when it is a petty offence even if connected with the offenders duties as an enrolled member`
  line `of the Force; or`
  line
  line `(iv) when, for reasons to be recorded in writing, it is not practicable for the Commandant invested`
  line `with the powers of a Magistrate to inquire into or try the offence,`
  line
  line `the offence may, if the prescribed authority within the limits of whose jurisdiction the offence has been`
  line `committed so requires, be inquired into or tried by an ordinary criminal court having jurisdiction in the`
  line matter.
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this section shall be construed to prevent any enrolled member of the Force`
  line `from being prosecuted under any other law for any offence made punishable by that law, or for being`
  line `liable under any such law to any other or higher penalty or punishment than is provided for such offence`
  line `by this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be punished twice for the same offence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (14627)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Application of Act 22 of 1922 to members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14627&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Police (Incitement to`
  line `Disaffection) Act, 1922 shall apply to members of the Force as it applies to members of a police force.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (14628)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Certain Acts not to apply to members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1985, s. 16, for section19 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14628&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Certain Acts not to apply to members of the Force.--Nothing contained in the Payment of`
  line `Wages Act, 1936 (4 of 1936), or the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or the Factories Act,`
  line `1948 (63 of 1948), or any corresponding law relating to investigation and settlement of industrial dispute`
  line `in force in a State shall apply to members of the Force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (14629)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Protection of acts of members of the Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. The words "superior officer or" omitted by s. 18 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14629&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any suit or proceeding against any ^1* * * member of the Force for any act done by him in the discharge of his duties, it shall be lawful for him to`
  line `plead that such act was done by him under the orders of a competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such plea may be proved by the production of the order directing the act, and if it is so`
  line `proved, ^1* * * the member of the Force shall thereupon be discharged from any liability in respect of the`
  line `act so done by him, notwithstanding any defect in the jurisdiction of the authority which issued such`
  line order.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for bed time being in force, any legal`
  line `proceeding, whether civil or criminal, which may lawfully be brought against any ^1* * * member of the`
  line `Force for anything done or intended to be done under the powers conferred by, or in pursuance of, any provision of this Act or the rules thereunder shall be commenced within the months after three act`
  line `complained of shall have been committed and not otherwise; and notice in writing of such proceeding and`
  line `of the cause thereof shall be given to the person concerned and his superior officer at least one month`
  line `before the commencement of such proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (14630)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=14630&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the classes and grades and the pay and remuneration of ^1*** members of the Force`
  line `and their conditions of service in the Force;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the powers and duties of ^1*** members of the Force authorised to exercise any`
  line `functions by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) fixing the period of service for ^1*** members of the Force;`
  line
  line `^2[(d) prescribing the description and quality of arms, accoutrements, clothing and other necessary`
  line `articles to be furnished to the members of the Force;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribing the places of residence of the member of the Force;`
  line
  line `(f) institution, management and regulation of any fund for any purpose connected with the`
  line `administration of the Force;`
  line
  line `(g) regulating the punishments and prescribing authorities to whom appeal shall be preferred from`
  line `orders of punishment, or remission of fines, or other punishments and the procedure to be followed`
  line `for the disposal of such appeals;`
  line
  line `(h) regulating matters with respect to Force custody under this Act, including the procedure to be`
  line `followed for taking persons into such custody;`
  line
  line `(i) regulating matters with respect to disposal of cases relating to offences under this Act and`
  line `specifying the places in which person convicted under this Act maybe confined;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which has to be, or may be, imposed or in respect of which rules are`
  line `required to be made under this Act.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "superior officers and" omitted by Act 60 of 1985, s. 17 (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for clauses (d) and (e) (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 17,ibid.,for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 20-9-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (86107)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Provisions as to existing Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-9-1985) on the directions of the Hon’ble High Court of Delhi in the matter of “P.K. Agrawal versus Union of India”, dated 28-01-2020. In the said section, the expression “this Act” occurring at both the places, refers to the Railway Protection Force (Amendment) Act, 1985 (60 of 1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103&sectionId=86107&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00001_195723_1517807317103
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Force constituted under the principal Act, as`
  line `functioning immediately before the commencement of this Act (hereafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `existing Force) shall, on such commencement, be deemed to be the Force constituted under the principal`
  line `Act as amended by this Act, and every member of the existing Force holding immediately before such`
  line `commencement an office mentioned in column (1) of the Table below shall, on such commencement be deemed to have been appointed to the office mentioned in the corresponding entry in column (2) of the`
  line `said Table.`
  line
  line Table
  line
  line `(1)(2)`
  line
  line `1. Director-General Director-General.`
  line
  line `2. Inspector-General-cum-Chief Security OfficerInspector-General.`
  line
  line `3. Additional Inspector-General-cum-Chief Security Officer. Additional Inspector General.`
  line
  line `4. Additional Inspector-General Additional Inspector General.`
  line
  line `5. Deputy Inspector-General-cum-Chief Security Officer.Deputy Inspector-General.`
  line
  line `6. Deputy Inspector-General Deputy Inspector-General.`
  line
  line `7. Principal, Training College Principal, Training College.`
  line
  line `8. Assistant Inspector-General. Assistant Inspector General.`
  line
  line `9. Deputy Chief Security Officer Senior Commandant Headquarters.`
  line
  line `10. Senior Security Officer. Senior Commandant.`
  line
  line `11. Security Officer Commandant.`
  line
  line `12. Staff Officer to Chief Security Officer Commandant-cum-Staff Officer to Chief`
  line `security Officer.`
  line
  line `13. Security Officer (Small Arms). Commandant (Small Arms).`
  line
  line `14. Commandant (Commandant.`
  line
  line `15. Assistant Security Officer Assistant Commandant.`
  line
  line `16. Personal Assistant to Chief Security Officer Assistant Commandant -cum-Personal`
  line `Assistant to Chief Security Officer.`
  line
  line `17. Adjutant Assistant Commandant Adjutant.`
  line
  line `18. Assistant Commandant Assistant Commandant.`
  line
  line `19. Principal, Training School Assistant Commandant-cum- Principal,`
  line `Training School.`
  line
  line `20.Vice-Principal, R.P.F. Training College Assistant Commandant-cum-VicePrincipal, R.P.F. Training College`
  line
  line `21. Inspector Inspector.`
  line
  line `22. Sub-Inspector Sub-Inspector.`
  line
  line `23. Assistant Sub-Inspector Assistant Sub-Inspector.`
  line
  line `24. Head Rakshak Head Constable.`
  line
  line `25. Battalion Havildar MajorHead Constable.`
  line
  line `26. Coy. Havildar Major Head Constable.`
  line
  line `27. Senior Rakshak Naik.`
  line
  line `28. Rakshak Constable.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), any member of the existing Force may,`
  line `within thirty days from the commencement of this Act, exercise his option by notice in writing to the`
  line Director-General.—
  line
  line `(a) if such member has been on deputation to the existing Force from any other service, to revert`
  line `to such other service, and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, to retire from service and an option so exercised shall be final, and a member exercising such option shall be permitted, within thirty days from the date on which he exercises such option to revert to the service from which he had been on deputation or, as the case may be, to retire from service.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— For the purposes of this section, the expression "member" includes an officer, and the`
  line `expression "Director-General" shall have the same meaning as in the principal Act as amended by this`
  line Act.]
